name: Bali Long Ago
address: Klumpu,Nusapenida, Nusa, Penida, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80771, Indonesia
review 1: Lovely, secluded place off the beaten track. Kids loved all the interesting creatures! Gordon likes hanging out in the rafters and Charlotte keeps guard of the path to the pool. The food is amazing, and there was always so much of it we fried the leftovers up for lunches!
review 2: An amazing Villa that offers you wonderful living spaces, gorgeous views, a perfect pool, and more. Owner is a pleasure to deal with and incredibly responsive. On site staff handle cleaning, driving and cooking when you want. We enjoyed breakfast multiple days, and the dinner we received our first night was phenomenal. Can't say enough GREAT things about Bali Long Ago! Hope to be back soon.
review 3: The best in nusa penida. It has Nice infinite pool over looking the island. They cooked dinner for us every night and we watched the sunset from up top as we ate. They had a scooter for us to rent and even helped us with laundry. In the middle of the jungle this was the ultimate experience I always wanted. I couldnâ€™t ask for more. They are very professional and answered quickly whenever we had a question. I definitely recommend this place.
review 4: Absolutely gorgeous location! The infinity pool with the view back toward Bali and Mt. Agung is perfect! The house has all the comforts of home, and the staff are friendly and helpful. Loved it here!
review 5: Gorgeous! Isolated and stunning. Sunset views. Pool is about 5 min walk from main building through lovely jungle path and has incredible views.
